//function signature--> includes function name, parameters, return type(defines how a function is called)

//hook --> special kind of react function which lets you hook into react features

//function call / function invocation -> it simply means calling the function/ hook
 useActionState(action, intialstate); => this is a function invocation while passing arguments


const [error, actionState, isPending] = useActionState(action, null);
This is a hook invocation with array destructuring assignment   -> In useActionState(action, null), action is the function the hook will execute, and null is the initial state for the action before it runs. The hook then returns [error, actionState, isPending], which we destructure into constants.


server component and client component
